name: Hill-View Bar and Restaurant

reviews.review_text:
The restaurant is tucked away in a serene and picturesque location, offering a perfect escape from the hustle and bustle of Goa. This is my personal favourite place, i visit this place every time when in goa.

The menu features a wide variety of Goan, Indian, and Continental dishes. The seafood is particularly fresh and flavorful, with standout dishes like the prawns curry, fish thali, lepo, modso and king fish. Their vegetarian options, such as the paneer tikka and vegetable biryani, are also excellent.

The flavors are rich and authentic, making every bite a treat for the taste buds.

Service is quick, worth it even if there is some waiting.  The restaurant offers stunning views of the surrounding hills and lush greenery. The first floor seating area is perfect for enjoying a meal while soaking in the natural beauty of Assagao.

Definitely a must visit place.

Had visited this place 10-12 years back. Was much smaller than, had better food and service. Always wanted to go back and finally when I got there last week it has totally changed in appearance. Seating has increased ten folds. The waiters seemed bored and talk to you in a transactional way. As it is the monsoon season, the variety of seafood available was very limited. We ordered chonak and it was fresh and tasty. Chicken and rice quantity was amazing. The bill was surprisingly low too. We were seated in the section that was more like a hut, also badly lit. However even after all this there were hordes of cars parked outside and people were rushing in even in the heavy down pour.

The Hill-View Bar and Restaurant Located in Xeldem, Curchorem locally know as "Annager" is a local Goan Restaurant. My friends and I visited this place on Sunday. They serve Goan Food at an affordable price. They have two seating areas one is upstairs which is for couple and family and other is on the ground floor for groups. They have a huge seating area. It's usually crowded during the weekends so the service is slow. They have a good parking area. It is recommended to visit early and give your order at one go and ask them to bring it one at a time. Taste wise food is good. I highly recommend Goan fish curry rice, tisreo and Chicken Tawa.

We ordered:
Tisreo
Chicken Sukka
Chicken Tawa
Chicken Tandoori
Rice Curry

Must visit place for Local Goan Food

description:
**Restaurant Review: Hill-View Bar and Restaurant, Sanguem**

Nestled amidst the lush greenery of Sanguem, Hill-View Bar and Restaurant boasts a commendable rating of **4.2** from an impressive **1,304 reviews**, making it a popular choice for locals and tourists seeking a delightful culinary experience. With tags such as **Goan (55)**, **thali (19)**, **fish curry (12)**, and **rates (20)** frequently mentioned, it’s clear that the restaurant has carved out a niche in serving up traditional Goan flavors alongside continental and Indian dishes, particularly excelling in their seafood offerings.

**Ambiance & Design**

From the moment you arrive, the enchanting surroundings create a tranquil haven, a welcome retreat from the vibrant hustle of Goa. The restaurant offers stunning views of the hills, as evidenced by the picturesque angles captured in customer photos. The decor feels authentic and rustic, reminiscent of classic Goan architecture, with natural wood embellishments and expansive seating that accommodates families and groups alike. Diners often note the soothing atmosphere, particularly on the first floor, where one can enjoy an unobstructed view of the lush landscape, making it an idyllic setting for a leisurely meal.

**Menu & Culinary Experience**

The expansive menu features a tantalizing mix of **Goan**, **Indian**, and **Continental** dishes. The standout selections include rich and flavorful **prawns curry**, mouthwatering **fish thali**, and succulent preparations of **king fish**. Vegetarian offerings, such as the aromatic **paneer tikka** and comforting **vegetable biryani**, don’t go unnoticed either, highlighting the restaurant's versatility in catering to various dietary preferences. Reviewers rave about the authentic Goan flavors, with each dish beautifully presented, often garnished with fresh herbs that further elevate the dining experience. 

Photos shared by guests capture the vibrant aesthetics of the dishes, showcasing the intricate details that reflect the chef’s dedication to culinary artistry. This commitment to quality is echoed in feedback highlighting the freshness of ingredients, particularly in the seafood section, which stays true to local flavors.

**Customer Experience & Service**

Dining at Hill-View is not just about the food; service plays an integral role in the overall experience. Many reviewers appreciate the friendly and quick service, even though some suggest that peak hours may result in longer wait times. The mention of staff’s transactional demeanor in some reviews hints at a need for warmth, which could further enhance the welcoming environment. Nevertheless, customers often leave satisfied, especially when they enjoy great value for money, as indicated in comments about the surprisingly low bills for large quantities.

**Popularity & Reviews**

Continuously buzzing with activity, Hill-View Bar and Restaurant is a hot spot, particularly on weekends. Despite occasional delays in service during peak periods, the allure of authentic Goan cuisine keeps diners returning. Critics often suggest visiting early, especially during monsoon season, when the variety of seafood may fluctuate. The combination of great food, scenic views, and affordable prices solidifies its reputation as a must-visit destination for anyone in the area.

**Conclusion**

In summary, Hill-View Bar and Restaurant delights with its blend of breathtaking surroundings, authentic Goan dishes, and a relaxed atmosphere perfect for soaking in the beauty of Sanguem. From the **Goan fish curry rice** to the delightful **thali** options, every visit promises to be a feast for the senses. While improvements in service could enhance the experience further, the heartwarming flavors and community feel make it a standout establishment that earns its place on any food lover’s itinerary while in Goa. Don’t forget to capture the moment with the vibrant dishes and stunning views—photography here is as rewarding as the meal itself.

Come for the food, stay for the view, and take a piece of Goa home with you in your memories.
